.TH GRAFANA-UTIL-DASHBOARD 1 "2026-04-03" "grafana-util 0.7.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
grafana\-util\-dashboard \- dashboard browse, export, import, inspection, governance, and screenshot workflows
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B grafana-util dashboard [\fISUBCOMMAND\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.PP
.B grafana-util db [\fISUBCOMMAND\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
grafana\-util dashboard is the namespace for live dashboard workflows, local draft handling, export/import review, inspection, topology, and screenshots. The same namespace is also available as grafana\-util db.
.PP
Use this namespace when you need to browse live dashboards, fetch or clone a live dashboard into a local JSON draft, compare local files with Grafana, inspect export or live metadata, convert raw dashboards into prompt JSON, or publish a prepared dashboard back to Grafana.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B browse
Open the live dashboard tree in an interactive terminal UI.
.TP
.B get
Fetch one live dashboard into an API\-safe local JSON draft.
.TP
.B clone\-live
Clone one live dashboard into a local draft with optional overrides.
.TP
.B list
List dashboard summaries without writing export files.
.TP
.B export
Export dashboards to raw/, prompt/, and provisioning/ files.
.TP
.B import
Import dashboard JSON files through the Grafana API.
.TP
.B patch\-file
Patch one local dashboard JSON file in place or write it to a new path.
.TP
.B review
Review one local dashboard JSON file without touching Grafana.
.TP
.B publish
Publish one local dashboard JSON file through the existing dashboard import pipeline.
.TP
.B delete
Delete live dashboards by UID or folder path.
.TP
.B diff
Compare local dashboard files against live Grafana dashboards.
.TP
.B inspect\-export
Analyze dashboard export directories with operator\-summary and report\-contract views.
.TP
.B inspect\-live
Analyze live Grafana dashboards via a temporary raw\-export snapshot.
.TP
.B inspect\-vars
List dashboard templating variables and datasource\-like choices from live Grafana.
.TP
.B governance\-gate
Evaluate governance policy against dashboard inspect JSON artifacts.
.TP
.B topology
Build a deterministic dashboard topology graph from JSON artifacts.
.TP
.B screenshot
Open one dashboard in a headless browser and capture image or PDF output.
.SH COMMON OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-url
Grafana base URL.
.TP
.B \-\-token, \-\-basic\-user, \-\-basic\-password
shared live Grafana credentials.
.TP
.B \-\-profile
load repo\-local defaults from grafana\-util.yaml.
.TP
.B \-\-color
control JSON color output for the namespace.
.SH WORKFLOW NOTES
.PP
Dashboard export intentionally separates output lanes for different workflows. Treat the raw export tree as the canonical replay or import source unless a command explicitly asks for another lane.
.PP
inspect\-export and inspect\-live are read\-only analysis commands, not mutation paths.
.PP
browse and screenshot operate against live Grafana state.
.SH EXAMPLES
.EX
grafana-util dashboard --help
.EE
.EX
grafana-util dashboard browse --profile prod
.EE
.EX
grafana-util dashboard browse --url http://localhost:3000 --basic-user admin --basic-password admin
.EE
.EX
grafana-util dashboard raw-to-prompt --input-file ./legacy/cpu-main.json --profile prod --org-id 2
.EE
.EX
grafana-util dashboard inspect-live --url http://localhost:3000 --token "$GRAFANA_API_TOKEN" --output-format governance-json
.EE
.EX
grafana-util dashboard inspect-live --url http://localhost:3000 --basic-user admin --basic-password admin --interactive
.EE
